content:
DelegateCompletionCallback Delegate

Definition

Represents the method that is called when an ActivityDelegate completes.

In this Article

public delegate void DelegateCompletionCallback(NativeActivityContext context, ActivityInstance completedInstance, IDictionary<string,object> outArguments);
Inheritance
Object
System.Delegate
DelegateCompletionCallback

Remarks

The values in the outArguments dictionary are the <xref:System.Activities.ActivityDelegateParameter> values of the ActivityDelegate that are assigned when the ActivityDelegate is invoked, keyed by <xref:System.Activities.ActivityDelegateParameter.Name%2A>.
